This paper proposes a new approach for detecting multiple anatomical landmarks in medical images using multi-agent reinforcement learning. The paper involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image analysis, artificial intelligence (AI) for the reinforcement learning approach, and machine learning (ML) for the Deep Q-Network (DQN) architecture. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of multi-agent systems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
